						<summary>

						<p>Slab lying in front of the Hanuman temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">1112 A.D.</hi> </p>						

						<p>It registers a gift of two <hi rend="italic">drammas</hi> (money) per month for the <hi rend="italic">gandha</hi> (sandal paste) to the god Rudrēśvara.</p>						

						<p>It stipulates that this dharma should be maintained by any person who becomes the officer of the temple from time to time. The slab is broken on the left side.</p>						

						<p>The date of the record and the doners are being the same as in No. 217 [A.R. 764].</p>						

						</summary>
